Cool.  What did you use for the regression?  Did you try using lower orders?

Did your compiler optimize those extraneous multiplications away for 
you?  If not, you should be able to get a bit more speed up..

   float xmul = (x &lt; 0.0f) ? -x : x; // better an &quot;x*=-1&quot;?
   float out = c0;
   out += c1*xmul;
   xmul *= x;
   out += c2*xmul;
   xmul *= x;
   out += c3*xmul;
   xmul *= x;
   out += c4*xmul;
   xmul *= x;
   out += c5*xmul;
   return (x &lt; 0.0f) ? 1.0f-out : out;

9 muls, 5 adds (vs. 15 muls, 5 adds)

